					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-598039#post-1637235</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-598039/scp-1722#post-1637235</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 04 Dec 2012 04:13:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Runic</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1340699</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I liked this, I thought it was funny. However, shit like this is why you rarely see any -j's. It infuriates me that something that was made with the clear intention of being funny was not tagged as a -j, which are specifically supposed to be funny. It wouldn't even take any effort on your part, just put &quot;-J&quot; at the end of the title. The fact that these kinds of articles are allowed to be posted on the mainlist with no objections is why so many -J's try to be super wacky and fail. Anything that's not completely absurd that's posted as a -J will be considered &quot;too bland&quot; because mainlisters like this are pretty much identical in tone to what they posted. Really, if stuff like this were -J's, it would only end up being positive.</p> <p>TL;DR should've been a -J, (removed because &quot;what is humor&quot;), no vote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
